en_891449_0	A total of 16 Officers and 215 Other Rankers of the 22 Division Headquarters at Trincomalee on the instructions of the General Officer Commanding (GOC), 22 Division attended a full-day workshop to learn about the ‘Dangers of Drug Addiction & Prevention from Its Use’ on Monday (29).
en_891449_1	The arrangement at the 22 Division Headquarters was aimed at educating all ranks about this social hazard and its implications on society.
en_891449_2	Mr Chamara Pradeep Karunaratne of National Dangerous Drug Control Board and the Senior Psychiatrist, Samantha Nilmalgoda at the invitation of the Directorate of Psychological Operations delivered lectures in this regard.
